{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:44.600759+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my investigation of the repository, here are the findings:\n\n---\n\n## Package Manager: **Yarn**\n\nThe repository expects contributors to use **Yarn**. Evidence:\n\n1. **`yarn.lock`** is committed to the repo (not `package-lock.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, etc.).\n2. **`Taskfile.yaml`** explicitly runs `yarn install` and `yarn release` in its `init` and `release` tasks.\n3. **`package.json`** has a `fix` script defined as `yarn lint --fix`, directly invoking `yarn`.\n\n---\n\n## Environment-Specific Script Names\n\nFrom **`package.json`** `scripts`:\n\n| Script | Description | Environment |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dev` | Local development server (`NODE_ENV=local`) | local |\n| `dev:stg` | Staging development server (`NODE_ENV=stg`) | staging |\n| `build` | Build for production (`--mode prod`) | production |\n| `build:stg` | Build for staging/test (`--mode test`) | staging |\n| `build:prod` | Build for production (`--mode production`) | production |\n| `serve` | Preview built output | — |\n| `lint` | ESLint check | — |\n| `fix` | ESLint auto-fix | — |\n| `deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages | — |\n\nFrom the **`envs/`** directory, there are three environment configuration files:\n\n| File | Environment |\n|---|---|\n| `.env.local` | Local development |\n| `.env.stg` | Staging |\n| `.env.prod` | Production |\n\nThe `Taskfile.yaml` `init` task copies `envs/.env.local` to `.env` as the default setup for new contributors, and then runs `yarn install`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 660, "prompt_tokens": 11213, "total_tokens": 11873, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 265, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10944, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "vid